    content: 'Describe a journey you remember well.',
    prompts: ['Where you went', 'Who you went with', 'How you traveled', 'Why it was memorable'],
    questions: ['Describe a journey you remember well.'],
    examples: [{ simple: 'I went to Beijing with my family last year.', band7: 'A journey that stands out in my memory is a road trip I took with three close friends along the southern coast last summer, covering about 500 kilometers over five days.' }],
    part2Example: { simple: 'I went to Beijing by train with my family. We visited the Great Wall and the Forbidden City. It was very fun.', band7: 'I\'d like to describe a train journey I took from Chengdu to Lhasa a couple of years ago. It was a 36-hour ride along the Qinghai-Tibet Railway, which is one of the highest railway lines in the world. I went with a university friend, and we had booked a soft sleeper compartment. The scenery was absolutely breathtaking — we passed through vast grasslands, snow-capped mountains, and crystal-clear lakes that seemed almost unreal. What made it truly memorable, though, wasn\'t just the landscape. It was the sense of adventure and the conversations we had with fellow passengers from different ethnic backgrounds. An elderly Tibetan woman shared her homemade butter tea with us and told us stories about life on the plateau. That journey taught me that sometimes the travel itself can be more meaningful than the destination.' },
