    questions: ['Describe a skill you learned that you are proud of.'],
    examples: [{ simple: 'I learned to cook Chinese food from my mother.', band7: 'A skill I\'m particularly proud of is public speaking — I went from being terrified of presenting in front of groups to winning a university debate competition.' }],
    part2Example: { simple: 'I learned to play the guitar. I practiced for one year. Now I can play many songs. I am proud because it was hard at first.', band7: 'I\'d like to describe a skill that took me a long time to master but that I\'m now very proud of — cooking. Growing up, I barely knew how to boil an egg, and I relied entirely on my parents or takeout food. The turning point came when I moved abroad for my studies and realized I needed to feed myself properly. I started with the absolute basics — following simple recipes on YouTube and making a lot of mistakes along the way. I burned countless dishes, oversalted soups, and once even set off the fire alarm making pancakes. But I was determined, so I kept at it. I began experimenting with different cuisines — Italian, Japanese, Thai — and gradually developed an intuitive understanding of flavors and techniques. After about two years, I could confidently host dinner parties for friends. What I\'m most proud of is not just the technical skill, but the creativity it has unlocked. Cooking has become my way of expressing care for others and exploring different cultures without leaving my kitchen.' },
