    prompts: ['Who this person is', 'What their job is', 'How they do their job well', 'What you can learn from them'],
    questions: ['Describe someone you know who is very good at their job.'],
    examples: [{ simple: 'My boss is very good at managing the team.', band7: 'Someone who stands out as exceptionally good at their job is our tech lead — she has an extraordinary ability to balance technical depth with business priorities, which is rare in the industry.' }],
    part2Example: { simple: 'My manager is very good at her job. She leads our team well. She always makes good decisions. I learn a lot from her.', band7: 'I\'d like to talk about our tech lead, who I consider one of the most competent professionals I\'ve ever worked with. She\'s been in the frontend field for over a decade, and her technical judgment is remarkable — she can evaluate a proposed architecture in minutes and spot potential scalability issues that the rest of us might miss entirely. What really sets her apart, though, is her approach to leadership. Instead of micromanaging, she creates an environment where everyone feels empowered to take ownership of their work. She runs code reviews that are genuinely educational rather than critical, and she has a gift for giving feedback that motivates rather than discourages. I\'ve learned so much from observing how she handles high-pressure situations — when a production incident occurs, she stays remarkably calm, methodically narrows down the problem, and communicates clearly with stakeholders. Watching her work has taught me that being truly good at your job isn\'t just about technical skill — it\'s about emotional intelligence, clear communication, and creating an environment where the whole team can perform at their best.' },
    relatedPart2Id: null, difficulty: 'medium', isCustom: false, isFavorite: false, createdAt: 0, updatedAt: 0,
