    prompts: ['Who this person is', 'What creative things they do', 'How they show their creativity', 'Why you think they are creative'],
    questions: ['Describe a person you know who is very creative.'],
    examples: [{ simple: 'My friend is a designer and she is very creative.', band7: 'The most creative person I know is a UI designer on my team who has an extraordinary talent for turning abstract requirements into intuitive, visually stunning interfaces.' }],
    part2Example: { simple: 'My friend Zhang is a designer. She draws beautiful pictures. She always has new ideas. I think she is very creative.', band7: 'I\'d like to talk about a UI designer I work with who I consider incredibly creative. She has this rare ability to take a vague product requirement — sometimes just a sentence or two from the product manager — and transform it into a design that not only meets the functional needs but also delights users. What strikes me about her creative process is that she doesn\'t just jump straight into design tools. She starts with extensive research — studying user behavior, analyzing competitors, and sketching dozens of rough concepts by hand before settling on a direction. I remember one project where we were redesigning a complex data dashboard. The original version was overwhelming, with dozens of charts and tables crammed onto one page. She came up with an elegant progressive disclosure approach that revealed information layer by layer, making it feel simple even though it contained the same amount of data. As a frontend developer, collaborating with her is a joy because her designs are not only beautiful but also technically thoughtful — she understands the constraints of web development and always provides detailed specifications. Her creativity has fundamentally changed how I think about the relationship between design and engineering.' },
